SEMDL Help Topic: reference normalize

Usage:
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> [--stdout]`
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> --dry-run`
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> --out <output.ssd> [--dry-run]`

Status:
- `--stdout` returns canonical inline output from `.ssd` with an optional paired `.ssm`.
- Bare apply and `--dry-run` rewrite or preview canonical inline output at the input path; paired input removes the sibling `.ssm`.
- `--out <output.ssd>` writes canonical inline output without modifying the source `.ssd` or paired `.ssm`.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help troubleshooting`

Sample:
- `ssd normalize docs/examples/normalize-source.ssd --out docs/examples/normalized-output.ssd`
